{
  "texts": [
    "In the discussion, rather than providing a recommended eye tracker for each persona, we want to model the process of making such a decision, thereby helping the readers ask the right questions and take responsibility for their own choices.",
    "Boris works in the field of decision-making.",
    "Part of his research is founded in the gaze cascade model, which predicts that the proportion of time a participant looks at the preferred option increases prior to a choice response (Shimojo, Simion, Shimojo, & Scheier, 2003).",
    "Potential applications of this model include product choice (Atalay, Bodur, & Rasolofoarison, 2012) and making choices in moral dilemmas (Pärnamets et al., 2015).",
    "Stimuli are presented on a computer screen where participants can choose between a few options that are large and well separated from each other."
  ]
}